{Old Crockern}
Old Crockern is supposed to be an old man who rides on a horse of bones around the area of Crockern Tor in Stormy weather. He is thought to warn speculators off the moor, to save the land form being ruined.
{The Lych Way}
This is an ancient route along which the dead of Lydford Parish were carried to be buried in the Church yard of Lydford Parish Church. On occasions monks attired in white habits can be seen in ghostly funeral processions, carrying a coffin along the track to Lydford.
